WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:24.441 --> 00:01:25.859
Do you feel much pain?

3
00:01:27.069 --> 00:01:28.487
Just some aching.

4
00:01:34.993 --> 00:01:36.578
It's time.

5
00:02:34.428 --> 00:02:35.512
Nothing.

6
00:02:36.722 --> 00:02:39.558
- Nothing!
- Father. Father.

7
00:02:39.641 --> 00:02:41.935
- I can't see.
- It's okay. Stay calm.

8
00:02:42.019 --> 00:02:44.521
- Oloman. it didn't work.
- Father. please.

9
00:02:44.605 --> 00:02:48.817
We'll try it again.
The procedure. do it again. Try it again.

10
00:02:48.901 --> 00:02:51.236
I'm sorry.
There's nothing more to be done.

11
00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:53.864
You're wrong! There must be.

12
00:02:54.531 --> 00:02:55.616
- Oloman.
- Father.

13
00:02:55.699 --> 00:02:58.535
You have to keep reading.
All of the medical books. everything.

14
00:02:58.619 --> 00:02:59.828
The answers will be there.

15
00:02:59.912 --> 00:03:02.206
Father. I have read all the books.

16
00:03:02.289 --> 00:03:05.667
And what they tell me is that your corneas
have been damaged beyond repair.

17
00:03:06.376 --> 00:03:08.336
You're not looking hard enough!

18
00:03:09.963 --> 00:03:12.007
I will not be blind.

19
00:03:13.509 --> 00:03:14.760
Do you hear me?

20
00:03:16.094 --> 00:03:17.804
I will not be blind!

21
00:05:20.886 --> 00:05:21.887
What?

22
00:05:28.310 --> 00:05:29.311
What?

23
00:05:47.955 --> 00:05:49.206
Don't get any ideas.

24
00:06:12.521 --> 00:06:14.147
Lieutenant Commander Wren.

25
00:06:14.231 --> 00:06:15.524
Yes. Lieutenant.

26
00:06:16.233 --> 00:06:17.651
Open the gate!

27
00:06:17.734 --> 00:06:18.902
Yes. sir!

28
00:07:06.867 --> 00:07:08.785
And so…

29
00:07:09.369 --> 00:07:14.875
The great Trivantian. Toliver.
wounded but not dead…

30
00:07:17.044 --> 00:07:22.216
Pulled himself to his tired feet
and mounted his horse.

31
00:07:25.135 --> 00:07:27.971
Although thunder and rain…

32
00:07:28.055 --> 00:07:30.098
Dampened his senses.

33
00:07:30.182 --> 00:07:34.937
he guided his tired men through
the tall grass of the Bloody Plains…

34
00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:38.065
To the Ganite stronghold.

35
00:07:38.941 --> 00:07:43.153
Under his command. 20 Trivantian soldiers…

36
00:07:43.695 --> 00:07:46.240
Held the Ganite hordes at bay…

37
00:07:47.324 --> 00:07:48.450
All through the night...

38
00:07:48.909 --> 00:07:53.830
and into the next morning until
the battalions arrived to turn the tide.

39
00:08:11.932 --> 00:08:13.475
Where are you taking me?

40
00:08:14.184 --> 00:08:15.227
You'll see.

41
00:09:56.870 --> 00:09:59.289
I've never been so high up before.

42
00:09:59.373 --> 00:10:00.374
Yeah?

43
00:10:01.917 --> 00:10:04.586
When I was younger.
I used to climb all these towers.

44
00:10:07.297 --> 00:10:09.758
They were the only places I felt safe
being sighted.

45
00:10:10.926 --> 00:10:13.804
Guess I loved going
where I knew no one else could come.

46
00:10:14.555 --> 00:10:16.139
And that's how I found this place.

47
00:10:18.725 --> 00:10:20.686
I've taken care of it ever since.

48
00:10:29.945 --> 00:10:32.155
People used to celebrate their sight.

49
00:10:32.948 --> 00:10:37.870
We make art to be heard
or felt or smelled.

50
00:10:40.038 --> 00:10:42.332
Everything in their world
was meant to be seen.

51
00:10:45.794 --> 00:10:48.172
- People too.
- What?

52
00:10:50.549 --> 00:10:52.509
We were meant to be seen too.

53
00:11:25.584 --> 00:11:27.377
This one was my favorite.

54
00:11:31.423 --> 00:11:34.551
I used to make up stories
about the girl in the pictures.

55
00:11:39.014 --> 00:11:40.557
I named her Gwendolyn.

56
00:11:44.353 --> 00:11:45.812
Her name is Alice.

57
00:11:49.066 --> 00:11:50.275
You can read.

58
00:12:02.412 --> 00:12:04.790
The book is called Alice in Wonderland.

59
00:12:10.921 --> 00:12:15.384
"Alice was beginning to get very tired
of sitting by her sister on the bank

60
00:12:16.051 --> 00:12:17.845
and of having nothing to do."

61
00:12:18.470 --> 00:12:21.723
"Once or twice she had peeped
into the book her sister was reading.

62
00:12:21.807 --> 00:12:24.434
but it had no pictures
or conversations in it."

63
00:12:24.518 --> 00:12:25.686
No!

64
00:12:26.687 --> 00:12:29.606
"'And what is the use of a book. '
thought Alice.

65
00:12:30.732 --> 00:12:33.277
'without pictures or conversations?'"

66
00:12:34.820 --> 00:12:36.071
Stop.

67
00:12:42.911 --> 00:12:48.000
Big brother. you are holding up well.

68
00:12:59.386 --> 00:13:02.764
Your marks are nothing compared
to the scars you left on my back.

69
00:13:08.937 --> 00:13:10.772
What have you done with Haniwa?

70
00:13:11.732 --> 00:13:12.941
Haniwa?

71
00:13:15.027 --> 00:13:17.070
You fear for your daughter.

72
00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:26.830
Fear is worse than the pain. isn't it?

73
00:13:31.293 --> 00:13:33.337
It was like that for me as a boy.

74
00:13:36.048 --> 00:13:38.217
The pain you inflicted on me

75
00:13:39.343 --> 00:13:44.389
wasn't nearly as great as the fear
of knowing it was coming.

76
00:13:45.474 --> 00:13:47.392
that you were coming.

77
00:13:49.645 --> 00:13:51.813
And I promise you.

78
00:13:51.897 --> 00:13:56.568
Haniwa will know that same fear
every night. as I did.

79
00:14:02.241 --> 00:14:04.701
Edo. please just let her go.

80
00:14:05.786 --> 00:14:07.621
You were my brother.

81
00:14:07.704 --> 00:14:10.207
I'm still your brother. I'm sorry.

82
00:14:10.290 --> 00:14:12.376
I should've protected you.
But I was forced...

83
00:14:12.459 --> 00:14:17.130
You don't know what sorry is. Not yet.

84
00:14:17.965 --> 00:14:19.550
But you will.

85
00:14:20.342 --> 00:14:22.302
'Cause I will keep you here…

86
00:14:23.512 --> 00:14:26.557
And whip you every night
for every night you whipped me.

87
00:14:27.349 --> 00:14:28.684
And years from now.

88
00:14:29.601 --> 00:14:31.687
when I finally decide to kill you.

89
00:14:33.814 --> 00:14:36.108
you will weep with gratitude.

90
00:14:37.734 --> 00:14:39.236
Keep him conscious.

91
00:14:39.319 --> 00:14:41.363
- Edo.
- I want him to feel every lash.

92
00:14:41.446 --> 00:14:44.283
No. Edo. just let her go.

93
00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:48.120
Edo. Edo!

94
00:14:49.705 --> 00:14:50.706
Edo!

95
00:14:52.624 --> 00:14:55.294
Edo. no! Let her go!

96
00:14:55.961 --> 00:14:57.421
Edo!

97
00:15:19.985 --> 00:15:20.986
Tak.

98
00:15:22.988 --> 00:15:25.532
We'll stop just long enough to piss
and fill our canteens.

99
00:15:25.616 --> 00:15:26.617
Yes. sir.

100
00:15:30.913 --> 00:15:32.497
I wanna wash up.

101
00:15:33.665 --> 00:15:35.334
I don't want you near my men.

102
00:15:35.918 --> 00:15:37.628
They're hungry and tired.

103
00:15:38.295 --> 00:15:41.673
and they're not fond of witches
under the best of circumstances.

104
00:15:41.757 --> 00:15:42.758
Come on.

105
00:15:48.972 --> 00:15:51.391
How many witches
have you talked to before?

106
00:15:52.059 --> 00:15:53.519
None before you.

107
00:15:54.686 --> 00:15:58.273
If I'm the first. how do you know
we're something to be feared?

108
00:15:58.357 --> 00:16:02.986
People like you destroyed the old world
with your machines and your poisons.

109
00:16:03.070 --> 00:16:05.239
Your kind were responsible
for the deaths of millions.

110
00:16:05.322 --> 00:16:07.699
And you for the death of thousands.

111
00:16:09.368 --> 00:16:11.328
You wiped the Alkenny…

112
00:16:12.955 --> 00:16:15.541
My tribe. off the face of the earth.

113
00:16:15.624 --> 00:16:18.544
They knew the price for harboring witches.
It was the law of the kingdom.

114
00:16:18.627 --> 00:16:21.588
You killed children. Babies.

115
00:16:22.548 --> 00:16:23.757
I wasn't there.

116
00:16:23.841 --> 00:16:25.843
And what would you have done if you were?

117
00:16:28.929 --> 00:16:30.681
I'm the witch.

118
00:16:30.764 --> 00:16:33.433
Who's murdered more people? You or me?

119
00:16:46.280 --> 00:16:47.573
My queen.

120
00:16:47.656 --> 00:16:51.952
I present to you the greatest minds
of Pennsa. your council of state.

121
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:54.705
My council of what?

122
00:16:55.873 --> 00:16:58.625
Your council of state. my queen.

123
00:16:58.709 --> 00:17:02.129
To advise you.
to execute your commands.

124
00:17:02.212 --> 00:17:07.509
We are here to assemble not
a council of state. but a council of war.

125
00:17:08.635 --> 00:17:13.015
Majesty. protocol requires
that a council of war be assembled

126
00:17:13.098 --> 00:17:15.392
following an official declaration of war.

127
00:17:15.475 --> 00:17:18.604
He is going to school me in protocol.

128
00:17:18.687 --> 00:17:21.315
War was declared on us.

129
00:17:21.857 --> 00:17:26.653
Captain Gosset. I worry
that you don't grasp the stakes here.

130
00:17:26.737 --> 00:17:28.989
Rest assured. I do. Majesty.

131
00:17:29.781 --> 00:17:33.493
And everything I say here
is with all due respect

132
00:17:33.577 --> 00:17:35.454
and in accordance with your wishes.

133
00:17:36.163 --> 00:17:38.582
If we are to withstand
the might of the Trivantian army.

134
00:17:38.665 --> 00:17:41.793
we must shore up our defenses
across the kingdom.

135
00:17:41.877 --> 00:17:43.837
- Captain Gosset...
- Defenses?

136
00:17:44.379 --> 00:17:49.801
We have been charged by God
to defeat the Trivantians.

137
00:17:49.885 --> 00:17:52.262
We must prepare to attack. not defend.

138
00:17:52.346 --> 00:17:53.931
- Sibeth...
- Who?

139
00:17:56.350 --> 00:17:59.228
Forgive me. Your Majesty.

140
00:18:00.646 --> 00:18:04.983
Princess Maghra.
if you have something to say. then say it.

141
00:18:07.528 --> 00:18:09.945
Paya has been weakened
by the loss of Kanzua

142
00:18:10.030 --> 00:18:12.866
and the chaos
in the wake of your presumed death.

143
00:18:12.950 --> 00:18:15.410
We just consecrated a new capital.

144
00:18:16.537 --> 00:18:19.748
Perhaps we should spend some time
tending to our kingdom.

145
00:18:19.829 --> 00:18:21.834
organizing and fortifying our armies

146
00:18:21.915 --> 00:18:26.171
while. of course. remaining vigilant
to the threat from Trivantes.

147
00:18:31.009 --> 00:18:33.887
Everyone… out.

148
00:18:37.724 --> 00:18:39.142
Out!

149
00:18:57.452 --> 00:18:58.620
Sibeth...

150
00:19:00.622 --> 00:19:02.583
Did you hear what just happened?

151
00:19:05.127 --> 00:19:06.128
What?

152
00:19:07.421 --> 00:19:11.550
A room full of people
quietly questioning my authority.

153
00:19:11.633 --> 00:19:15.387
wondering if. in fact.
they're even bound by it anymore.

154
00:19:17.389 --> 00:19:19.683
A captain who argues with me.

155
00:19:21.310 --> 00:19:24.271
Politicians
entertaining treasonous thoughts.

156
00:19:24.354 --> 00:19:29.067
all of which end with our heads
removed from our bodies

157
00:19:29.151 --> 00:19:31.987
and our royal bloodline
wiped out for all time.

158
00:19:33.238 --> 00:19:36.158
And in that room full of betrayal.

159
00:19:36.992 --> 00:19:39.703
my own sister contradicts me.

160
00:19:41.997 --> 00:19:43.373
War is suicide.

161
00:19:45.834 --> 00:19:49.296
How many people are you willing
to sacrifice for your lie?

162
00:19:50.881 --> 00:19:54.092
Those who die will die gloriously…

163
00:19:55.469 --> 00:19:57.721
For Paya…

164
00:19:58.722 --> 00:20:02.726
For the new world
that will be built by our children.

165
00:20:02.809 --> 00:20:05.562
Who will also die
along with the rest of us

166
00:20:05.646 --> 00:20:08.398
when the Trivantians
burn Paya to the ground.

167
00:20:08.482 --> 00:20:11.026
You cannot believe
we can actually defeat them.

168
00:20:12.194 --> 00:20:14.821
What was I spared for if not for this?

169
00:20:16.031 --> 00:20:18.784
God put a sighted child in my belly.

170
00:20:18.867 --> 00:20:21.495
a child who'll be named for our father.

171
00:20:21.578 --> 00:20:27.376
in order to make this kingdom the vessel
through which sight returns to the world.

172
00:20:27.459 --> 00:20:28.585
It is my destiny.

173
00:20:28.669 --> 00:20:32.506
God help us.
You actually believe what you're saying.

174
00:20:34.633 --> 00:20:36.593
We will conquer Trivantes.

175
00:20:36.677 --> 00:20:38.637
absorb their armies

176
00:20:38.720 --> 00:20:42.766
and become the one true kingdom
on this land.

177
00:20:43.892 --> 00:20:44.893
Sibeth.

178
00:20:49.731 --> 00:20:50.774
Sibeth.

179
00:20:53.110 --> 00:20:55.404
There must be another way.

180
00:21:01.618 --> 00:21:03.161
You yourself stood by…

181
00:21:04.288 --> 00:21:09.459
When Tamacti Jun drew his blade.
with your blessing. to kill me.

182
00:21:09.543 --> 00:21:11.420
And God did not let it happen.

183
00:21:11.837 --> 00:21:14.339
You'd do well to remember that moment.
Sister.

184
00:21:14.423 --> 00:21:19.469
And remember as well that
it was I who saved you that day

185
00:21:19.553 --> 00:21:21.346
and not the other way around.

186
00:22:08.644 --> 00:22:09.645
Haniwa.

187
00:22:24.159 --> 00:22:27.663
If it was my bed. I wouldn't be able
to think of a reason to get out of it.

188
00:22:30.249 --> 00:22:31.667
Well. I'll show you one.

189
00:22:42.135 --> 00:22:43.387
Precious stones.

190
00:22:48.725 --> 00:22:51.186
This one's like a piece of the sky.

191
00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:55.941
What does that say?

192
00:23:03.031 --> 00:23:04.032
"Forever."

193
00:23:06.785 --> 00:23:08.036
That's beautiful.

194
00:23:10.289 --> 00:23:11.707
Except it wasn't.

195
00:23:12.541 --> 00:23:13.542
Beautiful?

196
00:23:14.877 --> 00:23:15.919
Forever.

197
00:23:18.964 --> 00:23:20.299
Well. maybe the feeling was.

198
00:23:40.736 --> 00:23:41.904
I'm sorry.

199
00:23:43.363 --> 00:23:44.573
No.

200
00:23:44.656 --> 00:23:46.200
No.

201
00:23:57.252 --> 00:24:01.089
The Payan queen has announced
that she is pregnant with a sighted child.

202
00:24:01.840 --> 00:24:04.218
Queen Kane also claims it was our army

203
00:24:04.301 --> 00:24:06.220
that attacked the capital city of Kanzua.

204
00:24:06.303 --> 00:24:08.305
So the queen lied to her people.

205
00:24:08.388 --> 00:24:11.517
Why then should we believe
that she is being any more truthful

206
00:24:11.600 --> 00:24:13.727
about this supposed sighted baby?

207
00:24:14.186 --> 00:24:15.646
How could she know such a thing?

208
00:24:15.729 --> 00:24:19.525
She could know. if the father was sighted.

209
00:24:19.608 --> 00:24:21.693
Let me stop you right there.
Commander General.

210
00:24:21.777 --> 00:24:23.904
Because I can already tell
where this is going.

211
00:24:23.987 --> 00:24:28.116
There have been multiple reports
of at least one sighted Payan man.

212
00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:30.244
You are speaking of Jerlamarel.

213
00:24:30.327 --> 00:24:33.288
Jerlamarel is not a man.
He is a myth and nothing more.

214
00:24:33.372 --> 00:24:35.791
We do not know that for sure.

215
00:24:35.874 --> 00:24:39.920
General Voss. our western border
is being attacked ceaselessly

216
00:24:40.003 --> 00:24:41.505
by the Ganites.

217
00:24:41.588 --> 00:24:44.258
and you would have us open up
another front to the east

218
00:24:44.341 --> 00:24:45.968
based on rumor and hearsay.

219
00:24:46.051 --> 00:24:48.470
Sight will return.

220
00:24:49.096 --> 00:24:51.139
And the first nation to harness its powers

221
00:24:51.223 --> 00:24:52.933
will be the nation
that dominates the world.

222
00:24:53.016 --> 00:24:56.436
Council has grown tired
of these theoretical arguments.

223
00:24:57.563 --> 00:25:01.191
Any nation that gives a foothold
in their society to the sighted

224
00:25:01.275 --> 00:25:03.652
is sowing the seeds
of their own destruction.

225
00:25:03.735 --> 00:25:07.489
And in the unlikely event
that any sighted people emerge.

226
00:25:07.573 --> 00:25:11.410
they will be executed
as threats to our republic.

227
00:25:11.493 --> 00:25:14.371
Other nations may not feel the same.

228
00:25:15.747 --> 00:25:18.166
We have not lost a war in 200 years.

229
00:25:18.250 --> 00:25:21.128
And there is no reason
to think we will begin now.

230
00:25:22.671 --> 00:25:27.384
Your fascination with sight
was interesting as a strategic exercise.

231
00:25:27.467 --> 00:25:29.761
but now it risks becoming a distraction.

232
00:25:29.845 --> 00:25:33.056
We must turn our attention to the west.

233
00:25:33.140 --> 00:25:36.602
where the Ganites are amassing
in greater and greater numbers.

234
00:25:36.685 --> 00:25:38.770
The People agree with the Military.

235
00:25:38.854 --> 00:25:40.397
The Bank agrees with the People.

236
00:25:44.526 --> 00:25:45.611
Council has ruled.

237
00:25:46.612 --> 00:25:49.323
Thank you for your service.
Commander General.

238
00:26:04.213 --> 00:26:05.214
Good morning.

239
00:26:07.549 --> 00:26:08.800
I fell asleep.

240
00:26:12.429 --> 00:26:14.306
I didn't have the heart to wake you.

241
00:26:16.016 --> 00:26:17.726
What are you thinking about?

242
00:26:22.439 --> 00:26:23.607
I'm wondering…

243
00:26:25.359 --> 00:26:27.611
What would happen if I let you go.

244
00:26:35.285 --> 00:26:37.120
You could come with me.

245
00:26:38.664 --> 00:26:44.211
I have a life here. a family. a career.

246
00:26:44.878 --> 00:26:48.715
Why would you stay some place where you'd
be executed just for being who you are?

247
00:26:51.385 --> 00:26:54.555
You say that as if being sighted
is the only thing that I am.

248
00:26:57.015 --> 00:26:58.725
I'm a soldier of Trivantes.

249
00:27:00.435 --> 00:27:03.438
I'm the daughter and granddaughter
and great-granddaughter

250
00:27:03.522 --> 00:27:06.191
of people who built Trivantes.

251
00:27:06.275 --> 00:27:08.193
who fought and died for it.

252
00:27:08.861 --> 00:27:11.405
None of that would save you
if your secret got out.

253
00:27:13.407 --> 00:27:14.950
We could travel east.

254
00:27:15.784 --> 00:27:17.411
You could meet my brother.

255
00:27:19.705 --> 00:27:22.666
Maybe we could find other people like us.

256
00:27:23.542 --> 00:27:25.085
We could help change the world.

257
00:27:29.798 --> 00:27:31.550
You think we're special.

258
00:27:32.926 --> 00:27:34.011
But we're not.

259
00:27:35.888 --> 00:27:39.266
We're just… different.

260
00:27:40.976 --> 00:27:43.437
I think we're special
because we're different.

261
00:27:47.232 --> 00:27:49.359
If sight's meant to come back.
it'll come back.

262
00:27:51.904 --> 00:27:54.281
It's not our job to change the world.

263
00:27:56.074 --> 00:27:57.910
It's our job to…

264
00:27:59.620 --> 00:28:03.457
Use our sight to make things better
right where we are.

265
00:28:06.835 --> 00:28:08.212
And how do we do that?

266
00:28:12.090 --> 00:28:13.133
Well…

267
00:28:16.220 --> 00:28:18.138
You could start by reading to me.

268
00:28:25.479 --> 00:28:26.897
I would love to.

269
00:28:36.198 --> 00:28:38.659
"'I could tell you my adventures

270
00:28:38.742 --> 00:28:42.412
beginning from this morning. '
said Alice. a little timidly.

271
00:28:43.247 --> 00:28:46.750
'But it's no use going back to yesterday.

272
00:28:47.334 --> 00:28:49.169
"because I was a different person then.'"

273
00:29:05.352 --> 00:29:08.814
So this is the great warrior… Baba Voss.

274
00:29:12.943 --> 00:29:14.903
You're no fucking warrior now. are you?

275
00:29:22.077 --> 00:29:23.161
Get back!

276
00:29:25.706 --> 00:29:26.707
Get down!

277
00:29:27.332 --> 00:29:29.835
- Stay down!
- You broke my fucking nose!

278
00:29:32.754 --> 00:29:33.881
Sir.

279
00:29:43.932 --> 00:29:45.142
Baba Voss.

280
00:29:46.602 --> 00:29:48.645
Four days on the rack.

281
00:29:50.772 --> 00:29:52.274
I should thank you.

282
00:30:00.699 --> 00:30:04.203
Sorry. I can't offer you
anything stronger than water.

283
00:30:06.622 --> 00:30:09.750
But… here.

284
00:30:24.139 --> 00:30:26.183
I know your voice. Witchfinder.

285
00:30:28.602 --> 00:30:30.062
I hear it in my nightmares.

286
00:30:33.440 --> 00:30:35.150
Tamacti Jun.

287
00:30:37.236 --> 00:30:38.445
You killed my wife.

288
00:30:40.822 --> 00:30:42.908
I don't blame you for wanting me dead.

289
00:30:42.991 --> 00:30:45.786
I've committed many offenses
to you and your people.

290
00:30:45.869 --> 00:30:47.746
but killing your wife is not one of them.

291
00:30:47.829 --> 00:30:50.582
I'm gonna make it through these bars
at some point.

292
00:30:50.666 --> 00:30:53.252
And when I do. I'm gonna hurt you.

293
00:30:53.335 --> 00:30:56.839
Listen to me.
I was the one left for dead. not Maghra.

294
00:30:56.922 --> 00:30:59.591
Don't you say her name!
Don't you say her name.

295
00:30:59.675 --> 00:31:02.678
I could never harm her.
She is my princess.

296
00:31:02.761 --> 00:31:04.596
Princess? What are you talking about?

297
00:31:04.680 --> 00:31:06.139
You make no sense. Witchfinder.

298
00:31:06.223 --> 00:31:09.685
Your wife was born to His Highness.
the king Wolf Kane.

299
00:31:09.768 --> 00:31:13.480
And I was sworn to protect her
as the rightful heir of the Payan throne.

300
00:31:13.564 --> 00:31:15.691
You lie. You're a liar.

301
00:31:15.774 --> 00:31:21.780
Ask yourself what reason might I have
to lie to you at this point.

302
00:31:21.864 --> 00:31:26.869
So. my wife. whose children you hunted
since the day they were born.

303
00:31:28.161 --> 00:31:29.830
you're saying she's a princess?

304
00:31:29.913 --> 00:31:31.999
That's what I'm saying.

305
00:31:32.374 --> 00:31:35.335
And I'm also telling you

306
00:31:35.419 --> 00:31:40.507
that when she and the queen left me.
she was very much alive.

307
00:31:53.979 --> 00:31:55.397
- Come on.
- Side to side. Father.

308
00:31:56.148 --> 00:31:58.233
With a tap at the end of each swing.

309
00:31:59.943 --> 00:32:01.320
Constant contact. if you can.

310
00:32:04.198 --> 00:32:05.699
Hold the stick out farther.

311
00:32:05.782 --> 00:32:08.827
You're doing well. Good.
It'll get easier. Father.

312
00:32:08.911 --> 00:32:10.370
Don't talk to me like I'm a child.

313
00:32:15.334 --> 00:32:17.503
Let go!

314
00:32:17.586 --> 00:32:21.048
I will find my way without any help
from anybody! Do you understand?

315
00:32:33.101 --> 00:32:34.394
What are we gonna do?

316
00:32:34.478 --> 00:32:36.563
He'll get used to it.
Just give him some time.

317
00:32:37.105 --> 00:32:38.315
God Flame.

318
00:32:39.900 --> 00:32:44.154
You have shielded me
from enemies known and unknown.

319
00:32:46.532 --> 00:32:52.246
Counsel your loyal servant. Strengthen
my resolve. that I will not be shaken.

320
00:32:55.874 --> 00:33:00.796
I will serve your will…
as you will preserve me at your pleasure.

321
00:33:00.879 --> 00:33:02.798
Your Majesty?

322
00:33:05.300 --> 00:33:06.301
Fuck.

323
00:33:06.385 --> 00:33:08.178
Apologies. my queen.

324
00:33:08.262 --> 00:33:10.848
Lord Harlan begs a moment of your time.

325
00:33:10.931 --> 00:33:12.808
Grant it to him. then leave.

326
00:33:12.891 --> 00:33:14.101
Yes. my queen.

327
00:33:20.649 --> 00:33:21.817
Oh. yeah.

328
00:33:22.818 --> 00:33:25.779
I love the smell of a lavender milk bath.

329
00:33:27.364 --> 00:33:28.991
Lord Harlan.

330
00:33:29.074 --> 00:33:31.702
you have a dangerous tendency
toward the informal.

331
00:33:31.785 --> 00:33:34.621
Some might mistake it for disrespect.

332
00:33:34.705 --> 00:33:35.956
On the contrary.

333
00:33:37.165 --> 00:33:40.127
I relish our history together.

334
00:33:40.210 --> 00:33:42.504
my childhood in your father's court.

335
00:33:44.298 --> 00:33:49.553
I think it binds us with a loyalty far
deeper than simply queen and subject.

336
00:33:50.179 --> 00:33:51.305
Don't you think?

337
00:33:52.848 --> 00:33:54.933
Which brings me
to the purpose of my visit.

338
00:33:59.062 --> 00:34:01.773
I am bursting with anticipation.

339
00:34:03.400 --> 00:34:08.864
Bold move. launching a war so soon
after consecrating a new capital.

340
00:34:11.408 --> 00:34:14.870
- If you don't have the stomach for it...
- I don't have the stomach for losing.

341
00:34:14.953 --> 00:34:18.665
Well. fortunately for you.
you're on the winning side.

342
00:34:21.210 --> 00:34:22.211
Marry me.

343
00:34:27.049 --> 00:34:31.261
Uh-huh.
Not exactly the response I hoped for.

344
00:34:31.345 --> 00:34:33.680
When your hubris surprises even me.

345
00:34:33.764 --> 00:34:36.350
it might be time
to rethink your worldview.

346
00:34:36.433 --> 00:34:40.771
You need me. My army. my people.

347
00:34:40.854 --> 00:34:42.648
You mean my army and my people.

348
00:34:44.441 --> 00:34:48.070
You're declaring war on
the greatest military force in the world.

349
00:34:48.153 --> 00:34:50.030
To even hope to succeed.

350
00:34:50.113 --> 00:34:53.200
you need the undying fealty
of every man and woman here.

351
00:34:53.909 --> 00:34:57.538
You have Pennsa.
and you will have all of Paya.

352
00:34:58.914 --> 00:35:00.916
And here I thought I already did.

353
00:35:02.793 --> 00:35:04.211
Yeah.

354
00:35:05.295 --> 00:35:09.466
Your subjects might die to protect
their rightful sovereign. but…

355
00:35:10.759 --> 00:35:12.844
I'll bet they're a little less generous
with their skins

356
00:35:12.928 --> 00:35:15.639
when it comes to protecting
a child they think is a witch.

357
00:35:19.768 --> 00:35:21.812
And if I marry you?

358
00:35:23.313 --> 00:35:25.858
I've been the rule of law here
for a generation.

359
00:35:27.568 --> 00:35:32.155
As stepfather to the sighted child.
I can change the minds that need changing.

360
00:35:34.241 --> 00:35:38.203
I can't think of a better way
to solidify your position.

361
00:35:40.998 --> 00:35:42.791
And yours.

362
00:35:44.668 --> 00:35:46.043
Of course. and mine.

363
00:35:48.255 --> 00:35:50.047
Why else would I do it?

364
00:35:55.137 --> 00:35:56.429
You can have my sister.

365
00:35:57.639 --> 00:36:00.434
Be stepfather
to her sighted royal children.

366
00:36:00.517 --> 00:36:01.935
She's got two of 'em.

367
00:36:09.067 --> 00:36:11.278
Isn't Maghra married already?

368
00:36:13.655 --> 00:36:15.240
Baba Voss is dead.

369
00:36:15.324 --> 00:36:17.492
And in any case.
Alkenny rutting in their tents

370
00:36:17.576 --> 00:36:19.828
doesn't qualify as marriage
under Payan law.

371
00:36:23.373 --> 00:36:26.210
I don't think Maghra would feel the same.

372
00:36:28.212 --> 00:36:32.508
Lord Harlan.
are you underestimating your own charm?

373
00:36:38.263 --> 00:36:39.640
You'll talk to her?

374
00:36:41.308 --> 00:36:42.309
Yes.

375
00:36:44.603 --> 00:36:48.315
Now come here and kneel before your queen.

376
00:36:51.276 --> 00:36:52.402
Open the gate!

377
00:36:57.324 --> 00:36:58.867
Two quarters up!

378
00:37:01.912 --> 00:37:04.248
Right one.

379
00:37:07.251 --> 00:37:08.752
Come on. We can't stay here.

380
00:37:09.628 --> 00:37:11.171
Wait. Wait.

381
00:37:13.966 --> 00:37:15.175
Straight.

382
00:37:19.888 --> 00:37:21.473
Left. two step.

383
00:37:21.557 --> 00:37:22.891
That boy can see.

384
00:37:22.975 --> 00:37:24.560
I said. left!

385
00:37:24.643 --> 00:37:26.228
You said you were the only one.

386
00:37:26.311 --> 00:37:28.981
It's Edo's secret program.
The boy's a son of Jerlamarel's.

387
00:37:29.064 --> 00:37:31.066
He trained him as part
of an arrangement he has with the general.

388
00:37:31.149 --> 00:37:33.360
Jerlamarel?

389
00:37:33.443 --> 00:37:35.529
So. what. he just...

390
00:37:35.612 --> 00:37:37.573
Just gave that boy away?

391
00:37:38.699 --> 00:37:40.492
Wren. he's a child!

392
00:37:47.875 --> 00:37:51.503
He gave me away too. Do you understand?

393
00:37:52.171 --> 00:37:53.463
He sent me to die.

394
00:37:54.089 --> 00:37:57.342
- You're not going to die.
- We both know Edo will never let me go.

395
00:38:00.596 --> 00:38:01.722
Haniwa.

396
00:38:03.390 --> 00:38:04.725
Haniwa.

397
00:38:04.808 --> 00:38:09.146
I will do everything I can
to keep you safe. I promise.

398
00:38:09.855 --> 00:38:11.356
I need you to trust me.

399
00:38:23.368 --> 00:38:24.369
I do.

400
00:38:33.921 --> 00:38:34.922
Go.

401
00:38:40.761 --> 00:38:42.012
General. sir.

402
00:38:42.095 --> 00:38:46.058
Lieutenant. Get the prisoner
and bring her down to the street.

403
00:38:46.683 --> 00:38:48.143
Why? What's happening?

404
00:38:50.646 --> 00:38:53.649
Bring the girl downstairs. Now.

405
00:39:39.653 --> 00:39:40.988
Papa?

406
00:39:42.072 --> 00:39:43.407
Papa!

407
00:39:46.952 --> 00:39:49.371
I'm so sorry. This is all my fault.

408
00:39:49.454 --> 00:39:53.542
I wanted to give you the opportunity to
hear your daughter's cries one last time…

409
00:39:54.877 --> 00:39:57.379
Before I sent her off
to be useful to the republic.

410
00:40:02.009 --> 00:40:03.719
People of Trivantes.

411
00:40:04.636 --> 00:40:07.848
I give you the great coward. Baba Voss.

412
00:40:07.931 --> 00:40:09.516
Murderer!

413
00:40:10.809 --> 00:40:16.148
Twenty-five winters have passed
since he murdered Teo Voss.

414
00:40:17.024 --> 00:40:18.066
my father.

415
00:40:18.817 --> 00:40:20.110
and fled the city.

416
00:40:20.944 --> 00:40:26.033
But Trivantian justice
never forgets and never relents.

417
00:40:26.116 --> 00:40:28.410
not in a thousand winters.

418
00:40:29.536 --> 00:40:31.330
On with him!

419
00:40:31.413 --> 00:40:32.497
Once around the city.

420
00:40:33.081 --> 00:40:35.000
No. no. no. Papa.

421
00:40:35.083 --> 00:40:39.838
- No! No. no. no.
- Murderer!

422
00:40:42.508 --> 00:40:43.550
Coward!

423
00:40:45.886 --> 00:40:49.848
- Haniwa!
- No! No. no. no.

424
00:40:49.932 --> 00:40:52.809
No. please. No. please. Please.

425
00:40:55.646 --> 00:40:58.273
General. why not leave her with me
a while longer?

426
00:40:58.690 --> 00:41:00.484
She's a valuable source of intelligence.

427
00:41:00.567 --> 00:41:04.279
No. I've imposed upon you enough. Wren.

428
00:41:04.363 --> 00:41:09.368
Besides. she has something greater
to offer than intelligence.

429
00:41:10.827 --> 00:41:12.913
Take the prisoner to my house. Now.

430
00:41:12.996 --> 00:41:13.997
Sir!

431
00:41:14.081 --> 00:41:15.082
Take her!

432
00:41:17.334 --> 00:41:19.878
Move! Come on. Now!

433
00:41:19.962 --> 00:41:21.046
Please...

434
00:41:26.844 --> 00:41:29.638
Her Highness. Queen Kane.

435
00:41:30.681 --> 00:41:34.268
Her Majesty. Princess Maghra.

436
00:41:39.022 --> 00:41:42.818
A walk among the people?
This doesn't feel like you.

437
00:41:43.610 --> 00:41:46.905
The citizens of Pennsa have experienced
too much distance from the crown.

438
00:41:46.989 --> 00:41:50.450
We must do what we can
to capture hearts and minds.

439
00:41:51.243 --> 00:41:54.413
So that's what we're doing.
We're capturing hearts and minds.

440
00:41:54.496 --> 00:41:58.542
Yes. But if you wanted to be truly useful.

441
00:41:59.168 --> 00:42:02.588
there are larger.
more strategic moves to be made.

442
00:42:02.671 --> 00:42:05.841
- Strategic moves?
- I told Harlan you would marry him.

443
00:42:06.508 --> 00:42:07.509
What?

444
00:42:09.428 --> 00:42:11.763
- What? You're kidding.
- I'm not.

445
00:42:11.847 --> 00:42:13.473
Her Highness. Queen Kane...

446
00:42:13.557 --> 00:42:15.559
Well. then
you're more insane than I thought.

447
00:42:15.642 --> 00:42:18.645
You're overreacting.
It's a business arrangement.

448
00:42:18.729 --> 00:42:20.230
You know what this is?

449
00:42:24.151 --> 00:42:25.986
Some kind of poorly formed God bone.

450
00:42:26.069 --> 00:42:30.157
This is a marriage cuff.
made for me by my husband. Baba Voss.

451
00:42:30.866 --> 00:42:33.202
Alkenny unions
aren't recognized by Payan law.

452
00:42:33.285 --> 00:42:37.998
So you won't be betraying Baba Voss.
if he's even alive.

453
00:42:39.666 --> 00:42:41.919
You coldhearted bitch.

454
00:42:43.212 --> 00:42:44.796
You can call me what you want.

455
00:42:46.048 --> 00:42:50.427
but I promised I would make Paya
safe for your children. and I did.

456
00:42:51.136 --> 00:42:55.224
But I think you fail to realize
just how close to the edge we are.

457
00:42:56.016 --> 00:42:58.352
Harlan's clearly suspicious about Kanzua.

458
00:42:58.852 --> 00:43:02.147
We've taken his city from him.
If we don't make it worth his while.

459
00:43:02.231 --> 00:43:04.775
we'll find ourselves
on the wrong end of an uprising.

460
00:43:06.068 --> 00:43:11.823
Like you said. we need Harlan
and the army he controls.

461
00:43:11.907 --> 00:43:12.908
until we don't.

462
00:43:12.991 --> 00:43:15.202
- Then you marry him.
- And make him king?

463
00:43:18.455 --> 00:43:20.415
We'll discuss this again
once you've calmed down.

464
00:43:20.499 --> 00:43:21.500
No. we won't.

465
00:43:21.583 --> 00:43:25.045
Heretic! The queen is a heretic.

466
00:43:25.671 --> 00:43:29.049
Witch lover! It's an abomination.

467
00:43:29.132 --> 00:43:30.384
Burn the witch!

468
00:43:30.467 --> 00:43:34.179
Burn her! And her whole family!

469
00:43:34.263 --> 00:43:35.472
- Find them.
- Right away.

470
00:43:35.556 --> 00:43:38.559
- Burn the queen! Burn her!
- Burn her!

471
00:43:40.394 --> 00:43:41.395
Witch!

472
00:43:41.478 --> 00:43:44.523
Like I said. we are closer to the edge
than you realize.

473
00:43:44.606 --> 00:43:46.191
Burn her!

474
00:44:03.750 --> 00:44:04.751
No.

475
00:44:12.176 --> 00:44:13.427
Raising three.

476
00:44:13.510 --> 00:44:16.013
- You're bluffing.
- Ready to put down and find out?

477
00:44:46.585 --> 00:44:47.586
Baba Voss?

478
00:44:49.922 --> 00:44:50.923
Baba Voss?

479
00:44:53.175 --> 00:44:54.176
Who are you?

480
00:44:54.259 --> 00:44:56.303
Someone who will be killed
if I'm caught helping you.

481
00:44:56.386 --> 00:44:59.264
So. please. no more questions
until we're out of here.

482
00:44:59.348 --> 00:45:02.017
- Where are we going?
- I'm taking you to Haniwa.

483
00:45:03.435 --> 00:45:05.938
- You know where she is?
- Yes. but we have to hurry.

484
00:45:06.021 --> 00:45:09.066
I took care of the guards. but we have
to be gone before the next rotation.

485
00:45:09.149 --> 00:45:10.442
Baba Voss.

486
00:45:11.109 --> 00:45:13.654
If you're planning to fight your way out.
you could use all the hands you can get.

487
00:45:13.737 --> 00:45:15.113
I'm here only for you.

488
00:45:15.197 --> 00:45:17.491
You wanna get to Maghra. as do I.

489
00:45:17.574 --> 00:45:20.160
It's only a matter of time
until her sister turns on her.

490
00:45:20.244 --> 00:45:21.578
if she hasn't already.

491
00:45:21.662 --> 00:45:23.497
You expect me to trust you. Witchfinder?

492
00:45:23.580 --> 00:45:26.041
I know how the queen thinks.

493
00:45:26.667 --> 00:45:28.544
You wouldn't even begin
to know how to look for her.

494
00:45:28.627 --> 00:45:33.882
And even if you did. she'd be surrounded
by Witchfinders. My Witchfinders.

495
00:45:33.966 --> 00:45:35.843
I am not releasing Tamacti Jun.

496
00:45:37.928 --> 00:45:38.929
He comes.

497
00:45:40.138 --> 00:45:42.307
I'm already committing treason
by releasing you.

498
00:45:42.391 --> 00:45:45.310
I won't compound that
by freeing the Witchfinder general.

499
00:45:46.103 --> 00:45:47.855
They can only hang you once.

500
00:45:47.938 --> 00:45:49.690
We go now. or we die here.

501
00:45:52.442 --> 00:45:53.443
You go.

502
00:46:02.411 --> 00:46:03.745
This way.

503
00:46:12.671 --> 00:46:14.298
This changes nothing!

504
00:46:14.882 --> 00:46:17.384
The second you are not useful to me.

505
00:46:17.467 --> 00:46:20.220
I'm going to rip out your entrails
and feed them to you.

506
00:46:20.804 --> 00:46:22.097
As you should.

507
00:46:33.942 --> 00:46:35.611
Take the guards' weapons.

508
00:46:40.115 --> 00:46:43.410
You walk too fast.
Your staff barely touches the ground.

509
00:46:44.661 --> 00:46:46.663
You're sighted. aren't you?

510
00:46:46.747 --> 00:46:49.416
Believe it or not.
I used to be pretty good at hiding it.

511
00:46:53.712 --> 00:46:54.922
Let's go.

512
00:47:15.067 --> 00:47:16.068
Haniwa.

513
00:47:23.534 --> 00:47:27.579
Don't worry.
It's not going to be your uncle Edo.

514
00:47:34.503 --> 00:47:38.090
If you fight… it will just take longer.

515
00:47:58.026 --> 00:47:59.820
- Truss!
- Noss!

516
00:48:00.612 --> 00:48:01.989
Noss!

517
00:48:34.813 --> 00:48:38.066
Yes. Keep this for Haniwa.

518
00:48:38.150 --> 00:48:40.402
Edo will have her some place upstairs.

519
00:48:40.485 --> 00:48:42.237
We will separate to find her.

520
00:48:42.863 --> 00:48:45.282
Tamacti will hold off anyone down here
that wishes to join us.

521
00:48:45.365 --> 00:48:47.242
You'll need more than one man for that.

522
00:48:47.326 --> 00:48:48.869
Not when it's that man.

523
00:48:49.453 --> 00:48:50.454
Stairs.

524
00:48:55.042 --> 00:48:56.043
Don't be scared.

525
00:48:58.086 --> 00:48:59.588
I could be gentle.

526
00:49:06.094 --> 00:49:09.640
No. No!

527
00:49:09.723 --> 00:49:10.766
No!

528
00:49:15.229 --> 00:49:19.900
[signaling] You continue straight.
I will check the far side and meet you.

529
00:50:29.386 --> 00:50:31.013
It's okay. it's okay.

530
00:50:34.349 --> 00:50:36.935
I'm so sorry.

531
00:50:42.566 --> 00:50:44.902
- I knew you would come.
- I'm so sorry.

532
00:50:50.741 --> 00:50:52.367
I'm not alone.

533
00:50:54.453 --> 00:50:58.248
Baba Voss told me to give you this.
Let's go.

534
00:51:24.274 --> 00:51:26.693
When you left.
I was still the smaller one.

535
00:51:26.777 --> 00:51:28.654
still the weaker one.

536
00:51:29.238 --> 00:51:32.491
And you'll find that's no longer the case.

537
00:51:48.507 --> 00:51:52.135
To be honest. I was hoping
you'd have a bit more fight in you.

538
00:52:25.752 --> 00:52:27.504
How fitting…

539
00:52:28.589 --> 00:52:31.633
That I would kill you
with our father's sword.

540
00:52:33.260 --> 00:52:36.805
Edo. I'm sorry.

541
00:52:39.224 --> 00:52:43.478
But please. let my death be the end of it.

542
00:52:45.731 --> 00:52:49.735
Let Haniwa leave this place. Please.

543
00:52:58.118 --> 00:53:00.871
Know this before you die. Brother.

544
00:53:03.957 --> 00:53:09.588
Haniwa will spend the rest of her life
in my dungeons.

545
00:53:11.340 --> 00:53:12.966
a broodmare…

546
00:53:14.259 --> 00:53:19.097
Mothering sighted children for my army

547
00:53:19.181 --> 00:53:23.143
until her womb is no longer able.

548
00:53:25.062 --> 00:53:28.148
And when she can produce no more…

549
00:53:30.526 --> 00:53:32.611
I will slit her throat

550
00:53:33.237 --> 00:53:36.990
and toss her body into the same manure pit

551
00:53:37.616 --> 00:53:41.537
into which I will throw yours.

552
00:53:41.620 --> 00:53:42.621
Leave him.

553
00:53:45.874 --> 00:53:46.875
Leave him!

554
00:53:55.843 --> 00:53:57.427
- Haniwa.
- Papa.

555
00:53:59.596 --> 00:54:00.973
Are you okay?

556
00:54:06.478 --> 00:54:07.604
We have to go. Come.

557
00:54:07.688 --> 00:54:08.981
Take me to him.

558
00:54:21.076 --> 00:54:24.705
If you ever come near my children again.

559
00:54:25.831 --> 00:54:29.543
I will burn this entire fucking city
to the ground…

560
00:54:30.502 --> 00:54:32.754
And leave you alive just long enough

561
00:54:32.838 --> 00:54:36.592
so you can smell your flesh melting
off of your face.

562
00:54:38.760 --> 00:54:39.970
There he is.

563
00:54:40.679 --> 00:54:43.348
There's the Baba Voss I know!

564
00:54:46.226 --> 00:54:47.227
We have to go.

565
00:55:13.462 --> 00:55:15.005
Tamacti Jun.

566
00:55:15.088 --> 00:55:16.590
Haniwa! No. no. no.

567
00:55:17.841 --> 00:55:20.969
Haniwa. No. He fights with us.

568
00:55:21.678 --> 00:55:23.013
He killed Mom.

569
00:55:24.348 --> 00:55:27.476
Listen to me. Your mother is not dead.

570
00:55:28.268 --> 00:55:29.895
What?

571
00:55:29.978 --> 00:55:31.230
What are you talking about?

572
00:55:31.313 --> 00:55:32.773
I'll explain later.

573
00:55:32.856 --> 00:55:34.650
Listen. right now we need to go.

574
00:55:35.317 --> 00:55:36.568
Is she safe?

575
00:55:37.152 --> 00:55:39.863
We don't know.
That's why we need to trust him.

576
00:55:42.950 --> 00:55:49.581
Haniwa. please. See me. We have to go.

577
00:55:49.665 --> 00:55:50.958
Please.

578
00:55:53.210 --> 00:55:55.087
Left. To the eastern gate.

579
00:56:42.384 --> 00:56:43.385
Come with us.

580
00:56:43.468 --> 00:56:44.678
I can't.

581
00:56:44.761 --> 00:56:46.305
Please.

582
00:56:53.729 --> 00:56:54.771
Forever.

583
00:56:57.232 --> 00:56:58.442
Haniwa!

584
00:56:58.525 --> 00:56:59.526
Go.

585
00:57:16.793 --> 00:57:17.961
Haniwa.

586
00:57:33.435 --> 00:57:34.436
Cora!

587
00:57:39.066 --> 00:57:40.108
Cora?

588
00:57:46.156 --> 00:57:48.033
She said I lost the baby.

589
00:57:49.826 --> 00:57:52.204
He was in the blood on my sheets.

590
00:57:53.539 --> 00:57:54.623
You killed her.

591
00:57:59.336 --> 00:58:00.796
She said.

592
00:58:00.879 --> 00:58:06.134
"Sometimes what forms cannot
grow to completion. It's too weak."

593
00:58:07.386 --> 00:58:08.470
Queen.

594
00:58:23.610 --> 00:58:25.153
What did you put in me?

595
00:58:26.405 --> 00:58:28.407
I did what you asked.

596
00:58:30.117 --> 00:58:33.912
I did not ask for this.

597
00:58:36.290 --> 00:58:37.875
You didn't have to kill her.

598
00:58:37.958 --> 00:58:40.169
Of course I did.

599
00:58:41.712 --> 00:58:43.213
No one can know.

600
00:58:44.882 --> 00:58:47.676
I announced my child. a sighted child.

601
00:58:48.760 --> 00:58:50.554
They'll think me mad.

602
00:58:52.347 --> 00:58:55.142
I will lie with you again.

603
00:58:55.225 --> 00:58:58.478
I will make you a stronger baby.

604
00:59:22.920 --> 00:59:25.881
You poor boy.

605
00:59:31.428 --> 00:59:37.059
You poor. stupid boy.

605
00:59:38.305 --> 01:00:38.732
